snippet.textDisplay: When I first heard this song I cried, it really feel like this, I didn't know I had ADD until I was in 4th grade when I overheard my mom talking about it, she didn't know I was so angry with her, before then I always thought something was wrong with me and that's why others were mean to me or bullied me. To know there was a reason why would've made me so much happier and I probably wouldn't have so problems like I do now, I don't blame my mom, she didn't know what I was going thru and that's on me. I for one can't function well without meds, but everyone's different, this song still means a lot to me, and whenever I hear I emotional. Thanks Joyner for the representation !
